OL,3,CCampaigners are 'cautiously pleased'
OL,4,Cafter Welsh Water revises Pontsarn
OL,5,Cplans
OL,7,FIan Boothroyd from Dwr Cymru Welsh
OL,8,FWater said: "We really welcomed the
OL,9,Ffeedback that we had from the initial
OL,10,Fconsultation. And as a result of that,
OL,11,Fwe've been able to change our plans,
OL,12,Fand hopefully significantly mitigate
OL,13,Fany concerns that they had.
OL,15,F"We're really hoping that they'll
OL,16,Fsupport the new plans we've got in
OL,17,Fplace, which we believe have
OL,18,Fsignificantly reduced the challenges
OL,19,Fthat there were around landscape and
OL,20,Fheritage."
